  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n      \t\t\t\t\t\u003cul\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cli id=\"Entry1\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cspan\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ca name=\"entry\" id=\"EntryAnchor\"\u003eanchor\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eUK media outlets \u003ca href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2024/nov/27/brightons-vertical-pier-i360-files-for-administration\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ereport\u003c/a\u003e that Brighton\u0026#39;s \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/tag/777162/british-airways-i360\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ei360\u003c/a\u003e tourist attraction has filed for administration. Initially launched as \u0026#34;British Airways i360,\u0026#34; the seaside 531-foot moving observation tower had great expectations of attracting huge crowds pinned on it when it \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/article/149957127/designers-of-the-london-eye-create-new-landmark-for-brighton\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eopened in August 2016\u003c/a\u003e as a \u0026#34;vertical pier.\u0026#34; (Critic Oliver Wainwright mocked it as a \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/article/149961542/a-great-throbbing-shaft-oliver-wainwright-on-brighton-s-british-airways-i360-tower\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u0026#34;great throbbing shaft\u0026#34;\u003c/a\u003e in his opening review.) The structure was designed by Marks Barfield, the architects behind the famed London Eye attraction.\u003cbr/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOperator Brighton i360 Ltd has reportedly accrued £51 million ($65 million USD) in debt.\u003cbr/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/7d/7dd4ee0552c52268ca0ab9836cf27dc3.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x13